FBIS4-39851 "drsov113_l_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 Kyrgyzstan `Epidemiological State of Emergency' Declared in Bishkek `Epidemiological State of Emergency' Declared in Bishkek LD1106153194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1300 GMT 11 Jun 94 LD1106153194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] An "epidemiological state of emergency" has been declared in Bishkek, Kirghizia's [Kyrgyzstan] capital. According to the Russian News Agency this measure has been taken in connection with the fact that there has been a considerable increase in the incidence of dysentery and typhoid fever in that city. Until further instructions, all markets and bazaars in Bishkek are being closed where public health requirements are not being complied with.
